speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Lock onto them, Artoo.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Master, General Grievous's ship is directly ahead. The one crawling with vulture droids.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I see it. Oh, this is going to be easy.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Odd Ball, do you copy?

speaker: ODD BALL
combinedline: Copy, Red Leader.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Mark my position and form your squad up behind me...

speaker: ODD BALL
combinedline: We're on your tail, General Kenobi. Set S-foils in attack position.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: This is where the fun begins.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Let them pass between us.

speaker: ODD BALL
combinedline: They're all over me. Get them off my-

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I'm gonna go help them out.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: No. No. They are doing their job so we can do ours

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Missiles. Pull up.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: They overshot us.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: They're coming around.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: All right, R4. No, no, no,no-, no. Nothing too fancy.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Surge all power units, R2. Stand by reverse thrusters.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: We got 'em, R2.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Flying is for droids.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I'm hit. Anakin?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I see them. Buzz droids.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: R4, be careful. You have a-

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Oh, dear.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: They're shutting down all the controls.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Move to the right so I can get a clear shot at them.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: The mission. Get to the command ship. Get the chancellor. I'm running out of tricks here. In the name of- Hold your fire! You're not helping.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I agree. Bad idea.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I can't see a thing. My cockpit's fogging. They're all over me. Anakin!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Move to the right.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Hold on, Anakin. You're gonna get us both killed. Get out of here. There's nothing more you can do.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I'm not leaving without you, Master.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Get him, R2. Watch out.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: R2, hit the buzz droid's centre eye.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Yeah, you got him!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Great, Artoo.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: The General's Command Ship is dead ahead.

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: SCREAM

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Well, have you noticed the shields are still up?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Sorry, Master.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Oh, I have a bad feeling about this.

speaker: BATTLE DROID
combinedline: There they are. Get 'em

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Artoo, locate the Chancellor.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: The Chancellor's signal is coming from right there. The observation platform at the top of that spire.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I sense Count Dooku...

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I sense a trap.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Next move?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Spring the trap.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Artoo, go back. I need you to stay with the ship.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Here, take this, and wait for orders.

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: What's the situation, Captain?

speaker: CAPTAIN
combinedline: TWO Jedi have landed in the main hangar bay. We're tracking them.

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: Just as Count Dooku predicted.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Destroyers!!

speaker: BATTLE DROID
combinedline: Drop your weapons! I said drop 'em. Roger roger rogerroger

speaker: BATTLE DROID
combinedline: Those are Jedi fighters all right.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Did you press the stop button?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: No, did you?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: No!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Well, there's more than one way out of here.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: We don't want to get out, we want to get moving.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Artoo... Activate elevator... 3-1-1-7-4. Come in, Artoo.

speaker: SUPER BATTLE DROID 1
combinedline: What's that?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Artoo, do you copy? Artoo, activate the elevator number 31174.

speaker: SUPER BATTLE DROID 2
combinedline: Get back to work. That nothing.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Activate the elevator number 31174. Artoo?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Always on the move.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Artoo, switch on the comlink. Artoo, can you hear me? Artoo.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Stop, stop! Artoo, we need to be going up.

speaker: DROID 1
combinedline: Hands up, Jedi!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Artoo, do you copy? Artoo, do you hear me? Artoo, we need to be going up, not down.

speaker: SUPER BATTLE DROID 1
combinedline: Hey you!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Now, that's better...

speaker: SUPER BATTLE DROID 1
combinedline: You stupid little astro droid!

speaker: DROID 1
combinedline: Uh oh..

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Oh, it's you...

speaker: SUPER BATTLE DROID
combinedline: My eyes my eyes!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What was that all about?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Well, Artoo has been...

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: No loose wire jokes...

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Did I say anything?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: He's trying!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I didn't say anything!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Chancellor.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Are you all right?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Count Dooku.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: This time we will do it together.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I was about to say that.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Get help! You're no match for him. He's a Sith Lord.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Chancellor Palpatine, Sith Lords are our specialty.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: Your swords, please. We don't want to make a mess of things in front of the Chancellor.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: You won't get away this time, Dooku.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: I've been looking forward to this.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: My powers have doubled since the last time we met, Count.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: Good. Twice the pride, double the fall.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Get-

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: I sense great fear in you, Skywalker. You have hate, you have anger, but you don't use them.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Good, Anakin, good.Kill him. Kill him now!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I shouldn't...

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Do it!! You did well, Anakin. He was too dangerous to be kept alive.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Yes, but he was an unarmed prisoner. I shouldn't have done that, Chancellor. It's not the Jedi way.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: It is only natural. He cut off your arm, and you wanted revenge. It wasn't the first time, Anakin. Remember what you told me about your mother and the Sand People. Now, we must leave before more security droids arrive. Anakin, there is no time. We must get off the ship before it's too late.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: He seems to be all right.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Leave him, or we'll never make it.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: His fate will be the same as ours.

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: Prepare for attack.

speaker: PILOT
combinedline: All batteries fire! Fire!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Elevator's not working,

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Artoo... ...Activate Elevator 3224.

speaker: PILOT
combinedline: Reverse stabilizers.

speaker: DROID PILOT
combinedline: Reversing stabilizers

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: YELL

speaker: PILOT
combinedline: Magnetize! Magnetize!

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: Fire the emergency booster engines.

speaker: PILOT
combinedline: We're leveling out, sir.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Easy... We're in a bit of a situation.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Did I miss something?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Hold on.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: What is that?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Uh, oops.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Artoo, Artoo, shut down the elevator!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Too late! Jump! Let's see if we can find something in the hangar bay that's still flyable. Come on.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Artoo, get down here. Artoo, do you copy?

speaker: BODYGUARD
combinedline: General, we found the Jedi. They're in hallway 328.

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: Activate ray shields.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Ray shields!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Wait a minute, how'd this happen! We're smarter than this.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Apparently not. I say patience.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Patience?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Yes, Artoo will be along in a few moments and then he'll release the ray shields...

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: See! No problem.

speaker: SUPER BATTLE DROID
combinedline: Don't move.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Do you have a plan B?

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: Ah yes. The Negotiator, General Kenobi. We've been waiting for you. That wasn't much of a rescue.

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: And Anakin Skywalker... I was expecting someone with your reputation to be a little older.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: General Grievous... You're shorter than I expected.

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: Jedi scum...

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: We have a job to do. Anakin, try not to upset him.

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: Your lightsabers will make a fine addition to my collection.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Not this time. And this time you won't escape.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Artoo.

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: Crush them! Make them suffer! Stay at your stations.

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [rapid beeping]

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: Don't bother with them. Keep the ship in orbit.

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: You lose, General Kenobi.

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: Time to abandon ship.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: All the escape pods have been launched.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Grievous. Can you fly a cruiser like this?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You mean, do I know how to land what's left of this thing?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Well?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Under the circumstances, I'd say the ability to pilot this thing is irrelevant. Strap yourselves in. Open all hatches, extend all flaps, and drag fins.

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: UH OH

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: We lost something.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Not to worry, we're still flying half a ship.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Now we're really picking up speed...

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Eight plus sixty. We're in the atmosphere...

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Grab that... Keep us level.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Steady.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Easy, Artoo.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Five thousand. Fire ships on the left and the right.

speaker: MALE VOICE
combinedline: We'll take you in

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Copy that.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Landing strip's straight ahead.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: We're coming in too hot.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Another happy landing.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Are you coming, Master?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Oh no. I'm not brave enough for politics. I have to report to the Council. Besides, someone needs to be the poster boy.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Hold on, this whole operation was your idea.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Let us not forget, Anakin, that you rescued me from the Buzz Droids. And you killed Count Dooku. And you rescued the Chancellor, carrying me unconscious on your back.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: All because of your training.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Anakin, let's be fair. Today, you were the hero and you deserve your glorious day with the politicians.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: All right. But you owe me one... and not for saving your skin for the tenth time...

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Ninth time... that business on Cato Nemoidia doesn't- doesn't count. I'll see you at the briefing.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Chancellor Palpatine, are you all right?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Yes, thanks to your two Jedi Knights. They killed Count Dooku, but General Grievous has escaped once again.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: General Grievous will run and hide, as he always does. He's a coward.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: But with Count Dooku dead, he is the leader of the Droid Army, and I assure you, the Senate will vote to continue the war as long as Grievous is alive.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Then the Jedi Council will make finding Grievous our highest priority.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Come along, R2

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: The Republic cannot praise you enough.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Thank you, Senator Organa.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: It couldn't possibly be as bad as all that.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Well, there, I agree with you. In fact, I could do with a tune-up myself.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: But the fighting will continue until General Grievous is spare parts...

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: Well, I will do everything I can with the Senate.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Excuse me.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: Certainly.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Oh, Anakin!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I've missed you, Padme.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: There were whispers... that you'd been killed.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I'm all right. It feels like we've been apart for a lifetime. And it might have been... If the Chancellor hadn't been kidnapped. I don't think they would have ever brought us back from the Outer Rim sieges.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Wait, not here...

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Yes, here! I'm tired of all this deception. I don't care if they know we're married.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Anakin, don't say things like that.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Are you all right? You're trembling. What's going on?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Something wonderful has happened. Ani, I'm pregnant.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: That's... Well that's wonderful

speaker: PADME
combinedline: What are we gonna do?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: We're not going to worry about anything right now, all right? This is a happy moment. The happiest moment of my life.

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: Yes, Lord Sidious.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: General Grievous... I suggest you move the separatist leaders to Mustafar.

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: It will be done, My Lord.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: The end of the war is near, General.

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: But the loss of Count Dooku?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: His death was a necessary loss. Soon I will have a new apprentice- one far younger and more powerful.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Ani, I want to have our baby back home on Naboo. We can go to the lake country where no one will know... where we can be safe. I can go early and fix up the baby's room. I know the perfect spot, right by the gardens.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You are so beautiful!

speaker: PADME
combinedline: It's only because I'm so in love...

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: No, no, it's because I'm so in love with you.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: So love has blinded you?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Well, that's not exactly what I meant...

speaker: PADME
combinedline: But it's probably true! Anakin, help me! What's bothering you?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Nothing... I remember when I gave this to you.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: How long is it going to take for us to be honest with each other?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: It was a dream.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Bad?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Like the ones I used to have about my mother just before she died.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: And?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: And it was about you.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Tell me.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: It was only a dream. You die in childbirth...

speaker: PADME
combinedline: And the baby?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I don't know.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: It was only a dream.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: ...I won't let this one become real.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: This baby will change our lives. I doubt the Queen will continue to allow me to serve in the Senate, and if the Council discovers you are the father, you will be expelled-.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I know, I know.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Do you think Obi-Wan might be able to help us?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: We don't need his help. Our baby is a blessing.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Premonitions... premonitions... Hm... these visions you have...

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: They are of pain, suffering, death...

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Yourself you speak of, or someone you know?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Someone...

speaker: YODA
combinedline: ...close to you?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Yes.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Careful you must be when sensing the future, Anakin. The fear of loss is a path to the dark side.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I won't let these visions come true, Master Yoda.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Death is a natural part of life. Rejoice for those around you who transform into the Force. Mourn them, do not. Miss them, do not. Attachment leads to jealousy. The shadow of greed, that is.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What must I do, Master Yoda?

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Train yourself to let go of everything you fear to lose.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: You missed the report on the Outer Rim sieges.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I'm sorry, I was held up. I have no excuse.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: In short, they are going very well. Saleucami has fallen, and Master Vos has moved his troops to Boz Pity.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What's wrong then?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: The Senate is expected to vote more executive powers to the Chancellor today.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Well, that can only mean less deliberating and more action. Is that bad? It will make it easier for us to end this war.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Be careful of your friend Palpatine.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Be careful of what?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: He has requested your presence.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What for?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: He would not say.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: He didn't inform the Council? That's unusual, isn't it?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: All of this is unusual, and it's making me feel uneasy.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I hope you trust me, Anakin.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Of course.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I need your help, son.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What do you mean?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I'm depending on you.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: For what? I don't understand.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: To be the eyes, ears and voice of the Republic. Anakin... I'm appointing you to be my personal representative on the Jedi Council.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Me? A Master? I am overwhelmed, sir, but the Council elects its own members. They'll never accept this.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I think they will... they need you more than you know.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Allow this appointment lightly, the Council does not. Disturbing is this move by Chancellor Palpatine.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I understand.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: You are on this Council, but we do not grant you the rank of Master.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What? ! How can you do this?? This is outrageous, it's unfair... How can you be on the Council and not be a Master?

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Take a seat, young Skywalker.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Forgive me, Master.

speaker: KI-ADI-MUNDI
combinedline: We have surveyed all systems in the Republic, but have found no sign of General Grievous.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Hiding in the Outer Rim, Grievous is. The outlying systems, you must sweep.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: We do not have many ships to spare.

speaker: KI-ADI-MUNDI
combinedline: What about the droid attack on the Wookiees?

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: It is critical we send an attack group there, immediately!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: He's right, that is a system we cannot afford to lose.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Go, I will. Good relations with the Wookiees, I have.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: It is settled then. Yoda will take a battalion of clones to reinforce the Wookiees on Kashyyyk. May the Force be with us all.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What kind of nonsense is this, put me on the Council and not make me a Master!?? That's never been done in the history of the Jedi. It's insulting!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Calm down, Anakin. You have been given a great honor. To be on the Council at your age... It's never happened before. The fact of the matter is you're too close to the Chancellor. The Council doesn't like it when he interferes in Jedi affairs.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I swear to you, I didn't ask to be put on the Council...

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: But it's what you wanted! Your friendship with Chancellor Palpatine seems to have paid off.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: That has nothing to do with this.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: The only reason the Council has approved your appointment is because the Chancellor trusts you.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: And?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Anakin, I am on your side. I didn't want to put you in this situation.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What situation?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: The Council wants you to report on all of the Chancellor's dealings. They want to know what he's up to.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: They want me to spy on the Chancellor? That's treason!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: We are at war, Anakin.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Why didn't the Council give me this assignment when we were in session?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: This assignment is not to be on record.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: The Chancellor is not a bad man, Obi-Wan. He befriended me. He's watched out for me ever since I arrived here.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: That is why you must help us. Anakin, our allegiance is to the Senate, not to its leader who has managed to stay in office long after his term has expired.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: The Senate demanded that he stay longer.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Yes, but use your feelings, Anakin. Something is out of place.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You're asking me to do something against the Jedi Code. Against the Republic. Against a mentor... and a friend. That's what's out of place here. Why are you asking this of me?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: The Council is asking you.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Anakin did not take to his assignment with much enthusiasm.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: It's very dangerous, putting them together. I don't think the boy can handle it. I don't trust him.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: With all due respect, Master, is he not the Chosen One? Is he not to destroy the Sith and bring balance to the Force?

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: So the prophecy says.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: A prophecy... that misread could have been.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: He will not let me down. He never has.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: I hope right you are.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Sometimes, I wonder what's happening to the Jedi Order... I think this war is destroying the principles of the Republic.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Have you ever considered that we may be on the wrong side?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What do you mean?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: What if the democracy we thought we were serving no longer exists, and the Republic has become the very evil we've been fighting to destroy?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I don't believe that. And you're sounding like a Separatist!

speaker: PADME
combinedline: This war represents a failure to listen... Now, you're closer to the Chancellor than anyone. Please, ask him to stop the fighting and let diplomacy resume.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Don't ask me to do that. Make a motion in the Senate, where that kind of a request belongs.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: What is it?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Nothing.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Don't do this... don't shut me out. Let me help you. Hold me... like you did by the lake on Naboo, so long ago... when there was nothing but our love... No politics, no plotting... no war.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You wanted to see me, Chancellor.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Yes, Anakin! Come closer. I have good news. Our Clone Intelligence Units have discovered the location of General Grievous. He's hiding in the Utapau system.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: At last, we'll be able to capture that monster and end this war.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I would worry about the collective wisdom of the Council if they didn't select you for this assignment. You are the best choice, by far. Sit down,

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Leave us.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Anakin, you know I'm not able to rely on the Jedi Council. If they haven't included you in their plot, they soon will.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I'm not sure I understand.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: You must sense what I have come to suspect... the Jedi Council want control of the Republic... they're planning to betray me.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I don't think...

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Anakin, search your feelings. You know, don't you?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I know they don't trust you...

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Or the Senate... or the Republic... or democracy for that matter.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I have to admit my trust in them has been shaken.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Why? They asked you to do something that made you feel dishonest, didn't they? They asked you to spy on me, didn't they?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I don't uh... I don't know what to say.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Remember back to your early teachings. "All who gain power are afraid to lose it." Even the Jedi.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: The Jedi use their power for good.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Good is a point of view, Anakin. The Sith and the Jedi are similar in almost every way, including their quest for greater power.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: The Sith rely on their passion for their strength. They think inwards, only about themselves.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: And the Jedi don't?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: The Jedi are selfless... they only care about others.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Did you ever hear the tragedy of Darth Plagueis the wise?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: No.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I thought not. It's not a story the Jedi would tell you. It's a Sith legend. Darth Plagueis was a Dark Lord of the Sith, so powerful and so wise he could use the Force to influence the midi-chlorians to create life... He had such a knowledge of the dark side that he could even keep the ones he cared about from dying.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: He could actually save people from death?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: The dark side of the Force is a pathway to many abilities some consider to be unnatural.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What happened to him?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: He became so powerful... the only thing he was afraid of was losing his power, which eventually, of course, he did. Unfortunately, he taught his apprentice everything he knew, then his apprentice killed him in his sleep. It's ironic he could save others from death, but not himself.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Is it possible to learn this power?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Not from a Jedi.

speaker: KI-ADI-MUNDI
combinedline: Palpatine thinks General Grievous is on Utapau?

speaker: ANAKIN
addressed: KI-ADI-MUNDI, OBI-WAN, MACE WINDU, YODA, CHEWIE
combinedline: A partial message was intercepted in a diplomatic packet from the Chairman of Utapau.

speaker: YODA
addressed: ANAKIN, KI-ADI-MUNDI, OBI-WAN, MACE WINDU, CHEWIE
combinedline: Act on this, we must. The capture of General Grievous will end this war. Quickly and decisively we should proceed.

speaker: ANAKIN
addressed: KI-ADI-MUNDI, OBI-WAN, MACE WINDU, YODA, CHEWIE
combinedline: The Chancellor has requested that I lead the campaign.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: The Council will make up its own mind who is to go, not the Chancellor.

speaker: YODA
addressed: KI-ADI-MUNDI, OBI-WAN, MACE WINDU, ANAKIN, CHEWIE
combinedline: A Master is needed, with more experience.

speaker: KI-ADI-MUNDI
addressed: OBI-WAN, MACE WINDU, ANAKIN, YODA, CHEWIE
combinedline: I concur. Master Kenobi should go.

speaker: YODA
addressed: KI-ADI-MUNDI, OBI-WAN, MACE WINDU, ANAKIN, CHEWIE
combinedline: I agree.

speaker: KI-ADI-MUNDI
addressed: OBI-WAN, MACE WINDU, ANAKIN, YODA, CHEWIE
combinedline: Aye

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Aye Very well. Council is adjourned.

speaker: CLONE COMMANDER GREE
combinedline: The droids have started up their main power generators.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Then now the time is, Commander.

speaker: CHEWIE
combinedline: GROWL

speaker: CLONE COMMANDER GREE
combinedline: Yes, sir.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You're going to need me on this one, Master.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Oh, I agree. However it may turn out just to be a wild bantha chase.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Master! I've disappointed you. I have not been very appreciative of your training... I have been arrogant and I apologize... I've just been so frustrated with the Council.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: You are strong and wise, Anakin, and I am very proud of you. I have trained you since you were a small boy. I have taught you everything I know. And you have become a far greater Jedi than I could ever hope to be. But be patient, Anakin. It won't be long before the Council makes you a Jedi Master.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Obi-Wan. May the Force be with you.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Good-bye, old friend. May the Force be with you.

speaker: CLONE COMMANDER CODY
combinedline: Fortunately, most of the cities are concentrated on this small continent here... on the far side.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I'll keep them distracted until you get there. Just don't take too long.

speaker: CLONE COMMANDER CODY
combinedline: Come on, when have I ever let you down?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Very well, the burden is on me not to destroy all the droids unil you arrive

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Save your energy.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I can't!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Don't give up, Padme.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Obi-Wan's been here, hasn't he?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: He came by this morning.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What did he want?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: He's worried about you. He says you're been under a lot of stress.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I feel lost.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Lost? What do you mean?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Obi-Wan and the Council don't trust me.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: They trust you with their lives.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Something's happening... I'm not the Jedi I should be. I want more, and I know I shouldn't.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: You expect too much of yourself.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I have found a way to save you.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Save me?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: From my nightmares.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Is that what's bothering you?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I won't lose you, Padme.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I'm not going to die in childbirth, Annie. I promise you.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: No, I promise you!

speaker: TION MEDON
combinedline: Greetings, young Jedi. What brings you to our remote sanctuary?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Unfortunately, the war.

speaker: TION MEDON
combinedline: There's no war here. Unless you've brought it with you.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: With your kind permission, I should like some fuel and to use your city as a base as I search nearby systems for General Grievous.

speaker: TION MEDON
combinedline: He is here. We are being held hostage. They are watching us.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I understand.

speaker: TION MEDON
combinedline: Tenth level, thousands of battle droids.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Tell your people to take shelter. If you have warriors, now is the time.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Take the Fighter back to the ship. I'm staying here. Tell Cody I've made contact.

speaker: ALIEN 2
combinedline: Is he bringing additional warriors?

speaker: TION MEDON
combinedline: He didn't say..

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: It won't be long before the armies of the Republic track us here. I am sending you to the Mustafar system in the Outer Rim. It is a volcanic planet. You will be safe there.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Safe? Chancellor Palpatine managed to escape your grip, General, without Count Dooku. I have doubts about your ability to keep us safe.

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: Be thankful, Viceroy, you have not found yourself in my grip... Your ship is waiting.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Hello, there!

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: General Kenobi, you are a bold one.

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: Kill him! Back away. I will deal with this Jedi slime myself.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Your move.

speaker: GENERAL GRIEVOUS
combinedline: You fool. I have been trained in your Jedi arts by Count Dooku. Attack, Kenobi. Army or not, you must realize you are doomed.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Oh, I don't think so.

speaker: CLONE COMMANDER CODY
combinedline: Master Windu, may I interrupt? General Kenobi has made contact with General Grievous, and we have begun our attack.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Thank, you Commander.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Anakin, deliver this report to the chancellor. His reaction will give us a clue to his intentions.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Yes, Master.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: I sense a plot to destroy the Jedi. The dark side of the Force surrounds the Chancellor.

speaker: KI-ADI-MUNDI
combinedline: If he does not give up his emergency powers after the destruction of Grievous, then he should be removed from office.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: The jedi council would have to take control of the senate in order to secure a peaceful transition.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: To a dark place this line of thought will carry us. Hmm... great care we must take.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Chancellor, we have just received a report from Master Kenobi. He has engaged General Grievous.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: We can only hope that Master Kenobi is up to the challenge.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I should be there with him.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: It is upsetting to me to see that the Council doesn't seem to fully appreciate your talents. Don't you wonder why they won't make you a Jedi Master?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I wish I knew. More and more I get the feeling that I am being excluded from the Council. I know there are things about the Force that they are not telling me.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: They don't trust you, Anakin. They see your future. They know your power will be too strong to control. You must break through the fog of lies the Jedi have created around you. Let me help you to know the subtleties of the Force.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: How do you know the ways of the Force?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: My mentor taught me everything about the Force... even the nature of the dark side.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You know the dark side?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Anakin, if one is to understand the great mystery, one must study all its aspects, not just the dogmatic, narrow view of the Jedi. If you wish to become a complete and wise leader, you must embrace a larger view of the Force. Be careful of the Jedi, Anakin. Only through me can you achieve a power greater than any Jedi. Learn to know the dark side of the Force and you will be able to save your wife from certain death.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What did you say?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Use my knowledge, I beg you...

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You're the Sith Lord!

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I know what has been troubling you... Listen to me. Don't continue to be a pawn of the Jedi Council! Ever since I've known you, you've been searching for a life greater than that of an ordinary Jedi... a life of significance, of conscience. Are you going to kill me?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I would certainly like to.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I know you would. I can feel your anger. It gives you focus, makes you stronger.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I am going to turn you over to the Jedi Council.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Of course you should. But you're not sure of their intentions, are you?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I will quickly discover the truth of all this.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: You have great wisdom, Anakin. Know the power of the dark side. The power to save Padme.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: So uncivilized...

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Master Windu, I must talk to you.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Skywalker, we just received word that Obi-Wan has destroyed General Grievous. We're on our way to make sure the chancellor returns emergency power back to the senate.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: He won't give up his power. I've just learned a terrible truth. I think Chancellor Palpatine is a Sith Lord.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: A Sith Lord?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Yes. The one we have been looking for.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: How do you know this?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: He knows the ways of the Force. He has been trained to use the dark side.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Are you sure?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Absolutely.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Then our worst fears have been realized. We must move quickly if the Jedi Order is to survive.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Master, the Chancellor is very powerful. You will need my help if you are going to arrest him.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: For your own good, stay out of this affair. I sense a great deal of confusion in you, young Skywalker. There is much fear that clouds your judgment.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I must go, Master.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: No. If what you've told me is true, you will have gained my trust. But for now, remain here. Wait in the council's chambers until we've returned.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Yes, Master.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: You do know, don't you, if the Jedi destroy me, any chance of saving her will be lost.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Master Windu. I take it General Grievous has been destroyed then. I must say, you're here sooner than expected.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: In the name of the Galactic Senate of the Republic, you are under arrest, Chancellor.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Are you threatening me, Master Jedi?

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: The Senate will decide your fate.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I am the Senate!

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Not yet!

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: It's treason, then.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: You are under arrest, My Lord.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Anakin! I told you it would come to this. I was right. The Jedi are taking over.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: The oppression of the Sith will never return. You have lost.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: No! No! No! You will die!

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: He's a traitor.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: He is a traitor!

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I have the power to save the one you love. You must choose.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Don't listen to him, Anakin!

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Don't let him kill me. I can't hold it any longer. I can't. I'm weak. I'm too weak. Anakin! Help me. Help me! I can't hold on any longer.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: I am going to end this once and for all.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You can't. He must stand trial.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: He has control of the senate and the courts. He's too dangerous to be left alive.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: But I'm too weak. Don't kill me. Please.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: It is not the Jedi way... He must live...

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Please don't, please don't...

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I need him...

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Please don't...

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: NO!

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Power! Unlimited power!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What have I done?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: You are fulfilling your destiny, Anakin. Become my apprentice. Learn to use the dark side of the Force.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I will do whatever you ask.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Good.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Just help me save Padme's life. I can't live without her.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: To cheat death is a power only one has achieved, but if we work together, I know we can discover the secret.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I pledge myself to your teachings.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Good. Good. The Force is strong with you. A powerful Sith you will become. Henceforth, you shall be known as Darth... Vader.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: Thank you. my Master.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Rise. Because the Council did not trust you, my young apprentice, I believe you are the only Jedi with no knowledge of this plot. When the Jedi learn what has transpired here, they will kill us, along with all the Senators.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: I agree. The council's next move will be against the Senate.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Every single Jedi, including your friend Obi-Wan Kenobi, is now an enemy of the Republic.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: I understand, Master.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: We must move quickly. The Jedi are relentless; if they are not all destroyed, it will be civil war without end. First, I want you to go to the Jedi Temple. We will catch them off balance. Do what must be done, Lord Vader. Do not hesitate. Show no mercy. Only then will you be strong enough with the dark side to save Padme.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: What about the other Jedi spread across the galaxy?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Their betrayal will be dealt with. After you have killed all the Jedi in the Temple, go to the Mustafar system. Wipe out Viceroy Gunray and the other Separatist leaders. Once more, the Sith will rule the galaxy, and we shall have peace.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Commander, contact your troops. Tell them to move to the higher levels.

speaker: CLONE COMMANDER CODY
combinedline: Very good, sir. Oh, by the way, I think you'll be needing this.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Thank you, Cody, Now let's get a move on. We've got a battle to win here.

speaker: CLONE COMMANDER CODY
combinedline: Yes, sir!

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Commander Cody, the time has come. Execute Order 66.

speaker: CLONE COMMANDER CODY
combinedline: Yes, My Lord. Blast him!

speaker: KI-ADI-MUNDI
combinedline: Come on!

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Execute Order 66.

speaker: CLONE PILOT
combinedline: It will be done, My Lord.

speaker: CLONE COMMANDER GREE
combinedline: It will be done, My Lord.

speaker: YOUNGLING
combinedline: Master Skywalker, there are too many of them. What are we going to do?

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: The Chancellor's office indicated Master Anakin returned to the Jedi Temple. Don't worry, I'm sure he'll be all right.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: What's going on here?

speaker: CLONE SERGEANT
combinedline: There's been a rebellion, sir. Don't worry, the situation is under control. I'm sorry, sir. It's time for you to leave.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: And so it is.

speaker: CLONE COMMANDER APPO
combinedline: Get him! Shoot him!

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: No!

speaker: AT-ST CLONE SERGEANT
combinedline: Don't worry about him. Let him go.

speaker: CLONE SERGEANT
combinedline: All these Wookiees are dead. Move to the east.

speaker: CLONE TROOPER
combinedline: Yes, sir.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Good-bye, Tarfull. Good-bye, Chewbacca. and Tarfful, miss you I will.

speaker: CHEWIE
combinedline: GROWLS TWICE

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Miss you, I will.

speaker: CHEWIE
combinedline: ROARS EIGHT TIMES IN TOTAL

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: Hopefully we will be able to intercept a few Jedi before they walk into this catastrophe.

speaker: CLONE CAPTAIN
combinedline: Did you find Kenobi?

speaker: CLONE TROOPER
combinedline: Sir, no one could have survived that fall.

speaker: CLONE CAPTAIN
combinedline: Start loading your men on the ships. Move it.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Emergency Code 913 ... I have no contact on any frequency.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: ...Master Kenobi...

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Repeat.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: Master Kenobi??

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Senator Organa! My Clone Troops turned on me... I need help.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: We have just rescued Master Yoda. It appears this ambush has happened everywhere. We're sending you our coordinates.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Hush! Not so loud!

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Are you all right? I heard there was an attack on the Jedi Temple... you can see the smoke from here.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: I'm fine. I'm fine. I came to see if you and the baby are safe.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: What's happening?

speaker: VADER
combinedline: The Jedi have tried to overthrow the Republic...

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I can't believe that!

speaker: VADER
combinedline: I saw Master Windu attempt to assassinate the Chancellor myself.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Oh Anakin, what are you going to do?

speaker: VADER
combinedline: I will not betray the Republic... my loyalties lie with the Chancellor and with the Senate... and with you.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: What about Obi-Wan?

speaker: VADER
combinedline: I don't know... Many Jedi have been killed. We can only hope that he's remained loyal to the Chancellor.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Anakin, I'm afraid.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: Have faith, my love. Everything will soon be set right. The Chancellor has given me a very important mission. The Separatists have gathered on the Mustafar system. I'm going there to end this war. Wait for me until I return. Things will be different, I promise. Please, wait for me.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Well, he is under a lot of stress, Artoo.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Take care, my little friend.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: My Lady, is there anything I might do?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: No thank you, Threepio.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: I feel so helpless.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: How many other Jedi managed to survive?

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Heard from no one, have we.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: I saw thousands of troops attack the Jedi Temple. That's why I went looking for Yoda.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Have we had any contact from the Temple?

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Received a coded retreat message, we have.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: It requests all Jedi to return to the Temple. It says that the war is over...

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Well, then we must go back! If there are other stragglers, they will fall into the trap and be killed.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Suggest dismantling the coded signal, do you?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Yes, Master. There is too much at stake

speaker: YODA
combinedline: I agree. And a little more knowledge might light our way.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: The plan has gone as you had promised, My Lord.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: You have done well, Viceroy. When my new apprentice, Darth Vader, arrives, he will take care of you.

speaker: PILOT
combinedline: We are receiving a message from the Chancellor's office, sir.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: Send it through.

speaker: PILOT
combinedline: Yes, sir.

speaker: MAS AMEDDA
combinedline: Senator Organa... the Supreme Chancellor of the Republic requests your presence at a special session of Congress.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: I will be there.

speaker: MAS AMEDDA
combinedline: He'll be expecting you.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: Could be a trap.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: No, I don't think so. The Chancellor will not be able to control the thousands of star systems without keeping the Senate intact.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: If a special session of Congress there is, easier for us to enter the Jedi Temple it will be.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: Artoo... stay with the ship.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Welcome, Lord Vader. We've been expecting you.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: ...and the Jedi Rebellion has been foiled.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: What's happened?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: The Chancellor's been elaborating on a plot by the Jedi, to overthrow the Senate.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: The remaining Jedi will be hunted down and defeated.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Not even the younglings survived.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Killed not by clones, this Padawan. By a lightsaber, he was.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Who? Who could have done this?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: The attempt on my life has left me scarred and deformed, but I assure you my resolve has never been stronger.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Stop! No!

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: In order to ensure our security and continuing stability, the Republic will be reorganized into the first Galactic Empire, for a safe and secure society

speaker: PADME
combinedline: So this is how liberty dies, with thunderous applause...

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: The war is over. Lord Sidious promised us peace... we only want...

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I've recalibrated the code warning all surviving Jedi to stay away.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: For the Clones to discover the recalibration, a long time it will take.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Wait, Master. There is something I must know...

speaker: YODA
combinedline: If into the security recordings you go, only pain will you find.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I must know the truth, Master. It can't be... It can't be...

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: You have done well, my new apprentice. Now, Lord Vader, go and bring peace to the Empire.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I can't watch anymore

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Destroy the Sith, we must.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Send me to kill the Emperor. I will not kill Anakin.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: To fight this Lord Sidious, strong enough, you are not.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: He is like my brother... I cannot do it.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Twisted by the dark side, young Skywalker has become. The boy you trained, gone he is... Consumed by Darth Vader.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I do not know where the Emperor has sent him. I don't know where to look.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Use your feelings, Obi-Wan, and find him, you will.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: When was the last time you saw him?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Yesterday.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: And do you know where he is now?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: No.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Padme, I need your help. He's in grave danger.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: From the Sith?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: From himself... Padme, Anakin has turned to the dark side.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: You're wrong! How could you even say that?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I have seen a security hologram of him killing younglings.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Not Anakin! He couldn't!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: He was deceived by a lie. We all were. It appears that the Chancellor is behind everything, including the war. Palpatine is the Sith Lord we've been looking for. After the death of Count Dooku, Anakin became his new apprentice.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I don't believe you... I can't.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Padme, I must find him.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: You're going to kill him, aren't you?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: He has become a very great threat.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I can't...

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Anakin is the father, isn't he? I'm so sorry.

speaker: CAPTAIN TYPHO
combinedline: My Lady, let me come with you.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: There is no danger. The fighting is over, and... this is personal.

speaker: CAPTAIN TYPHO
combinedline: As you wish, My Lady... but I strongly disagree.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I'll be all right, Captain.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: This is something I must do myself. Besides, Threepio will look after me.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Oh, dear.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Do you know, that I think I'm beginning to get the hang of this flying business.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: The Separatists have been taken care of, My Master.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: It is finished then. You have restored peace and justice to the galaxy. Send a message to the ships of the Trade Federation. All droid units must shut down immediately.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: Very good, My Lord.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: I saw your ship... What are you doing out here?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I was so worried about you. Obi-Wan told me terrible things.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: What things?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: He said you have turned to the dark side... that you killed younglings.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: Obi-Wan is trying to turn you against me.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: He cares about us.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: Us?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: He knows... He wants to help you. Anakin, all I want is your love.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: Love won't save you, Padme. Only my new powers can do that.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: At what cost? You are a good person. Don't do this.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: I won't lose you the way I lost my mother! I am becoming more powerful than any Jedi has ever dreamed of and I'm doing it for you. To protect you.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Come away with me. Help me raise our child. Leave everything else behind while we still can.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: Don't you see, we don't have to run away anymore. I have brought peace to the Republic. I am more powerful than the Chancellor. I can overthrow him, and together you and I can rule the galaxy. Make things the way we want them to be.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I don't believe what I'm hearing... Obi-Wan was right. You've changed.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: I don't want to hear any more about Obi-Wan. The Jedi turned against me. Don't you turn against me.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I don't know you anymore. Anakin, you're breaking my heart. You're going down a path I can't follow.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: Because of Obi-Wan?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Because of what you've done... what you plan to do. Stop, stop now. Come back! I love you.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: Liar!

speaker: PADME
combinedline: No!

speaker: VADER
combinedline: You're with him. You brought him here to kill me!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Let her go, Anakin!

speaker: PADME
combinedline: No! Anakin.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Let her go.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: You turned her against me.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: You have done that yourself.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: You will not take her from me.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Your anger and your lust for power have already done that. You have allowed this Dark Lord to twist your mind until now... until now you have become the very thing you swore to destroy.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: Don't lecture me, Obi-Wan. I see through the lies of the Jedi. I do not fear the dark side as you do. I have brought peace, freedom, justice, and security to my new Empire.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Your new Empire?

speaker: VADER
combinedline: Don't make me kill you.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Anakin, my allegiance is to the Republic... to democracy.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: If you're not with me, then you're my enemy.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Only a Sith deals in absolutes. I will do what I must.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: You will try.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: I hear a new apprentice, you have. Emperor, or should I call you Darth Sidious?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Master Yoda. You survived.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Surprised?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Your arrogance blinds you, Master Yoda. Now you will experience the full power of the dark side. I have waited a long time for this moment, my little green friend. At last the Jedi are no more.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Not if anything to say about it, I have. At an end your rule is and not short enough it was. If so powerful you are, why leave?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: You will not stop me. Darth Vader will become more powerful than either of us.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Faith in your new apprentice, misplaced may be, as is your faith in the dark side of the Force.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Hurry. Careful timing we will need.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: Activate your homing beacon when you're ready.

speaker: CLONE COMMANDER THIRE
combinedline: There is no sign of his body, sir.

speaker: MAS AMEDDA
combinedline: Then he is not dead.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Double your search.

speaker: CLONE COMMANDER THIRE
combinedline: Yes sir. Right away, sir.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Tell Captain Kagi to prepare my shuttle for immediate takeoff.

speaker: MAS AMEDDA
combinedline: Yes, Master.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I sense Lord Vader is in danger.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Into exile I must go. Failed, I have.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I have failed you, Anakin. I have failed you.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: I should have known the Jedi were plotting to take over.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Anakin, Chancellor Palpatine is evil.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: From my point of view, the Jedi are evil.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Well, then you are lost!

speaker: VADER
combinedline: This is the end for you, My Master.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: It's over, Anakin. I have the high ground.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: You underestimate my power!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Don't try it. You were the Chosen One! It was said that you would, destroy the Sith, not join them. Bring balance to the Force, not leave it in darkness.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: I hate you!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: You were my brother, Anakin. I loved you.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Master Kenobi! We have Miss Padme on board. Please, please hurry. We should leave this dreadful place.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Obi-Wan. Is Anakin all right?

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: WHISTLES SOFTLY

speaker: CLONE CAPTAIN
combinedline: Your Majesty, this way. There he is.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: He's still alive. Get a medical capsule, immediately.

speaker: CLONE CAPTAIN
combinedline: Yes sir. Right away.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: Excuse me, Master Yoda. Obi-Wan Kenobi has made contact.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: We'll take her to the medical center, quickly.

speaker: MEDICAL DROID
combinedline: Medically, she's completely healthy. For reasons we can't explain, we are losing her.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: She's dying?

speaker: MEDICAL DROID
combinedline: We don't know why. She has lost the will to live. We need to operate quickly if we are to save the babies.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: Babies?

speaker: MEDICAL DROID
combinedline: She's carrying twins.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Luke.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Oh, Luke.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: It's a girl.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: ...Leia. Obi-Wan? There's good in him. I know. I know there's...still...

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Lord Vader, can you hear me?

speaker: VADER
combinedline: Yes, Master. Where is Padme? Is she safe, is she all right?

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: It seems, in your anger, you killed her.

speaker: VADER
combinedline: I? I couldn't have. She was alive! I felt it! No!

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Hidden, safe, the children must be kept.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: We must take them somewhere the Sith will not sense their presence.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Split up, they should be.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: My wife and I will take the girl. We've always talked of adopting a baby girl. She will be loved with us.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: And what of the boy?

speaker: YODA
combinedline: To Tatooine. To his family, send him.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I will take the child and watch over him.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Until the time is right, disappear we will.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Master Kenobi, wait a moment. In your solitude on Tatooine, training I have for you.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Training?

speaker: YODA
combinedline: An old friend has learned the path to immortality.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Who?

speaker: YODA
combinedline: One who has returned from the netherworld of the Force to train me... your old Master.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Qui-Gon?

speaker: YODA
combinedline: How to commune with him. I will teach you.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: Captain Antilles.

speaker: CAPTAIN ANTILLES
combinedline: Yes, Your Highness.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: I'm placing these droids in your care. Treat them well. Clean them up. Have the Protocol Droid's mind wiped.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: What?

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Oh, no.
